727108f-a.text:
1. Junction Boulevard (foreground), west side, just south of Thirty-Fourth Ave. (at the right, not seen), showing a side and rear view of the Charles Leverich house. At the left, note the private entrance to the estate. This house was demolished in June 1928. See other views for more data. March 1923.

2. The same, showing a private drive to the mansion. March 1924.

3. The same, another angle. March 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727107f-b.text: Junction Boulevard, at the S.E. corner of 34th Avenue, showing Public School No. 15, formerly the Union School. Mr. Armbruster states that the school was moved from its original site across the street. View 1: 1925. Eugene M. Armbruster Collection. View 2: October 19, 1935. P. L. Sperr.
